## Exchange Key Flow (User Journey)

```
User connects exchange in Settings -> ExchangeConnections component
           |
POST /api/trading/exchange-keys
{exchange: "alpaca", api_key: "...", api_secret: "..."}
           |
Backend validates keys against exchange API (get_account_balance)
           |
Fernet encrypt both keys
           |
Store in ExchangeAPIKey table
           |
Return {success, exchange, balance_usd} — NEVER return the keys
           |
Trading agent decrypts in memory only when executing trades
```

**How exchanges work for users:**
- Users bring their OWN exchange accounts (Alpaca/Binance/OANDA)
- Their money stays in THEIR exchange account — Unitrader never holds funds
- Unitrader is a software tool — not a broker, no FCA licence required
- Each exchange covers different asset classes:
  - Alpaca -> US stocks & ETFs
  - Binance/Coinbase -> Crypto
  - OANDA -> Forex

